title: $:/plugins/rimir/kind/doc/architecture
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Schema model

|!Element |!Stored as |!Discovery |
|Type |One tiddler with fields `kind.type`, `kind.caption`, `kind.icon`, `kind.namespaces`, `kind.title-formula`, `kind.stream-fields`, `kind.fields` (JSON) |`[has[kind.type]has[kind.fields]]` |
|Field def |Entry inside the type's `kind.fields` JSON array |`[<type-tid>get[kind.fields]jsonindexes[]]` |
|Instance |Any tiddler with `kind.type: <type-key>` |`[kind.type<type-key>]` |

There are no separate per-field tiddlers, no inheritance slots, no enum tiddlers. The type tiddler is the single source of truth for its schema.

!! Namespace mechanism

* Each type's `kind.namespaces` field is a space-separated list of namespace tokens — a type can belong to many at once.
* The active namespace lives in `$:/config/rimir/kind/active-namespace` (single value; empty = all).
* All UI surfaces that enumerate types — //creator//, //overview//, //validator// — filter via the `kind.belongs-to-ns` function in `engine.tid`.

!! Field types (`typed` values)

|!`typed` |!Editor |!Storage |
|`text` |single-line `<$edit-text>` |plain string |
|`longtext` |textarea |plain string |
|`number` |numeric input |plain string |
|`date` |`<$edit-date>` |TW date format |
|`datetime` |`<$edit-date>` with time |TW datetime format |
|`url` |single-line `<$edit-text type="url">` |plain string; live format check requires `http://` or `https://` prefix |
|`email` |single-line `<$edit-text type="email">` |plain string; live format check `local@domain.tld` |
|`phone` |single-line `<$edit-text type="tel">` |plain string; live format check for German numbers (`+49` or `0` prefix) |
|`enum` |single: `<$select>`; multi: pill toggle row |single string or list-field |
|`ref` |typeahead (filter input + dropdown + selected pills with ×) |single tiddler title or list-field |
|`$title` |read-only |computed from `kind.title-formula` |
|`$calculated` |read-only |computed from the field's `formula` |

Extension point: `field-input.tid` is one `<%if [<typed>match[X]]%>` cascade. Adding a field type = one new branch.

!! Constraints

|!Constraint |!Meaning |
|`required` |Must have a value (blocking) |
|`min:N` |Min N characters (text/longtext/url/email/phone) or N entries (multi-enum / multi-ref) |
|`max:N` |Max N characters or entries |
|`unique` |Unique among instances of the same type |
|`unique:wiki` |Unique wiki-wide (across all tiddlers) |
|''(intrinsic)'' |`url` / `email` / `phone` fields carry a built-in format check that fires when the value is non-blank. See `kind.viol-format-url` / `-email` / `-phone` in `engine.tid`. Regex patterns live in `_patterns.tid`. |

The validator reports any violation as a row in its bulk report. The editor shows live error messages below each input.

Save gating: the in-tiddler creator's Create button is disabled when `kind.any-invalid` returns non-empty (the disabled expression appends `then[yes]` because TW's `$button` widget only treats the literal string `"yes"` as truthy). The cascade-palette flows (`+ New <kind>` and spawn `+ Create new <ref-kind>`) emit a Warning row in place of the Save leaf when `any-invalid` fires — same dispatch pattern as the title-empty Warning row. Warning rows carry `"ca-after-fire":"keep"` so Enter is a no-op (the palette stays open and the user can keep editing).

!! Title generation

When `kind.title-formula` is set, the creator computes a new instance's title by evaluating the formula against the draft state tiddler:

```
\function kind.eval-title(type-tid, target-tid)
  [<type-tid>get[kind.title-formula]]
  :map[<target-tid>subfilter<currentTiddler>]
```

Example formula: `[get[parent]][[/]][get[abbrev]]+[join[]]` produces `parent-title/abbrev` style titles.

!! Stream-view (ViewTemplate auto-registration)

`viewtemplate.tid` is tagged `$:/tags/ViewTemplate` with `list-after: $:/core/ui/ViewTemplate/title`. On any tiddler with a `kind.type` field, it renders `stream-view.tid`, which reads `kind.stream-fields` from the type and emits a compact bar. Empty/missing `kind.stream-fields` = bar renders nothing (self-disabling).

A click on a field cell opens a popup containing the field's editor; a top-bar toggle switches to inline-edit mode (the editor replaces the cell directly).

!! Shared infrastructure

* ''engine.tid'' — all shared functions: type discovery, namespace filtering, JSON field-array accessors, constraint extraction, validation predicates, display helpers (truncation, ref resolution), title-formula evaluation
* ''field-input.tid'' — typed-dispatch input widget used by editor, stream-view popup, stream-view inline, and type-builder live preview
* ''editor.tid'' — 2-column table editor; takes only `target-tid` in scope; transcludes field-input per row

